Data Description
This article mainly discusses the COVID-19 situation and affection to South Africa in 2021 (until Aug 29, 2021). The data in this article is downloaded from Our World in Data1.



The Fact of COVID-19 Cases in South Africa
Until Aug 29, total COVID-19 cases in South Africa have reached over 2.6 million, and deaths cases over 77 thousand. From table 1, the new COVID-19 cases trend is generally a straight line every month. This indicates there are almost average new cases every day. The average number of new deaths cases is very different each month. By sorting the New Deaths/day column, January 2021 has the most deaths cases with a 509 per day averagely, and April 2021 has the least with 50 deaths per day. From the New Deaths Trend/month, except for February, March, and June, the other months fluctuate around the average deaths case number. February, March, and June have an unusual peek at someday.



